{"embedModel":"nomic-embed-text","dim":768,"count":4,"chunks":[{"text":"To install Gluu Server on Ubuntu, add the Gluu repository, then run apt-get install gluu-server. Start it with /sbin/gluu-serverd start and run setup.py.","source":"https://gluu.org/docs/gluu-server/installation/","title":"Installation"},{"text":"Gluu supports OpenID Connect. Register clients via the oxAuth admin UI or the client registration endpoint. Configure redirect URIs and scopes.","source":"https://gluu.org/docs/gluu-server/openid-connect/","title":"OpenID Connect"},{"text":"Gluu 5 (Flex) is a cloud-native rewrite using Janssen, deployed on Kubernetes. Gluu 4 is the monolithic VM-based server. Migration tooling is provided.","source":"https://github.com/GluuFederation/flex/blob/main/docs/index.md","title":"Gluu 4 vs 5"},{"text":"Custom authentication scripts (interception scripts) are written in Jython. Add them under Configuration > Scripts in the admin UI and enable the script.","source":"https://gluu.org/docs/gluu-server/admin-guide/custom-script/","title":"Custom Scripts"}],"vectors":""}